Definition: In this task, you are given an impractical statement. You are also given three reasons (associated with "A", "B", "C") explaining why this statement doesn't make sense. You must choose the most corresponding reason explaining why this statement doesn't make sense.

Positive Examples.input:
I sting a mosquito
(A) A human is a mammal
(B)A human is omnivorous
(C)A human doesn't have stings
Positive Examples.explanation: The third option explains why a human can't sting a mosquito correctly. So, the third option is the best choice.

Positive Examples.input:
He drinks apple.
(A) Apple juice are very tasty and milk too
(B)Apple can not be drunk
(C)Apple cannot eat a human
Positive Examples.explanation: The second option is the most reasonable choice.

Positive Examples.input:
Jeff ran 100,000 miles today
(A) 100,000 miles is way to long for one person to be able to run in one day.
(B)Jeff is a four letter name and 100,000 has six numerical digest
(C)100,000 miles is longer than 100,000 km.
Positive Examples.explanation: The first option is the best choice.

Negative Examples.input:
He drinks apple.
(A) Apple juice are very tasty and milk too
(B)Apple can not be drunk
(C)Apple cannot eat a human
Negative Examples.explanation: Do not generate anything else apart from one of the following characters: 'A', 'B', 'C'.

Negative Examples.input:
